<subSubSection pageNumber="494" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="494">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="494">Note:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
designated by Hitchcock (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="494">Contr. U.S. Natl. Herb. Wash.</emphasis>
12: 124. 1908), 100.5 (LINN), does not belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="L. var. virginicus" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Elymus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="virginicus" variety="virginicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="494">E. virginicus</emphasis>
L. var. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="494">virginicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as currently understood, and Campbell (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="494">Taxon</emphasis>
45: 128. 1996) therefore proposed the name for conservation with a conserved type. The proposal was eventually declined by the Committee for Spermatophyta (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="494">Taxon</emphasis>
54: 1094. 2005) but Campbell (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="494">Sida</emphasis>
22: 493. 2006) has indicated a desire to revisit the question.
</paragraph>
